<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   BROGAN _ Mary Brogan, wife of Florida Lt. Gov. Frank Brogan,
died Sunday following a two year struggle with cancer. She once
thought she was in remission, only to have the disease recur in her
breast and then in her brain. A tireless campaigner and supporter
of her husband, she was a teacher when she met Frank, then
superindent of the school district. Gov. Jeb Bush ordered all flags
at half-staff today in her memory. (Crowley, Palm Beach Post) 18.
</P>
<P>
   TV-CHILDREN _WASHINGTON _ The quality of children's television
has begun to improve, a new study finds, but problems of violence
and dubious ``educational'' claims persist. (Dart, Cox News
Service) 25. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washngton and (e) entertainment categories.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICAL
</P>
<P>
   BUSH _ Gov. George W. Bush airlifts his presidential dream to
California this week, a state rich with opportunity but fraught
with political peril. The opportunity for Bush lies in a vote-rich
Hispanic community he has targeted and a cash-rich high-tech
community that seems up for grabs. But for Bush, and all GOP
contenders, the California peril lies in a fractured state party
that is reeling from defeats. (Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This MOVED for Sunday papers but is still good for use on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION
</P>
<P>
   This budget will be updated at 6 p.m. EDT and afterwards as
necessary based on news developments.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTOS, LAYOUTS and GRAPHICS Stories that have photos, graphics
or page layouts will be posted on the Cox Server in folders
matching the category and slug. (Exception: Bureau photos are
available only through the Atlanta Location, Washington Bureau
desk, slugged to match the story.) Pages marked as CoxNet pages are
also available through Locations in the WAN desk of the AJC's
database.
</P>
<P>
   All times are Eastern unless otherwise noted. If stories will
move after 8 p.m. Eastern, an ETA will be given.
</P>
<P>
   If stories, photos, graphics or layouts will not move or will
move late, we'll send an advisory on the wire.
</P>
