<SLUG> BC-GEN-TIDBITS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WE LIKE LISTS, ESPECIALLY A BIG BOOK OF 'EM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Stuff that'll continue to amaze you and maybe even
your friends pulled from the pages of a book called Ultimate Sports
Lists (DK Publishing, by Mike Meserole, $17.95, 224 pgs):
</P>
<P>
   __The Lakers won five NBA titles in the 1980s, but actually
finished second to Boston in regular-season victories that decade.
OK, so it was only by one, 592 to 591.
</P>
<P>
   __During the '70s, the Pittsburgh Steelers (99-44-1) won four
Super Bowls, but the Los Angeles Rams (98-42-4) had a better record
in the regular season.
</P>
<P>
   __When the Seattle Mariners move from the cavernous Kingdome to
Safeco Field in two weeks, Dodger Stadium will be the fifth-largest
major-league baseball park, with a 56,000 capacity.
</P>
<P>
   __Maury Wills' record 104 stolen bases with the Dodgers in 1962
now stands at only No.7 all-time.
</P>
<P>
   __The Dodgers are the only major-league baseball team of the
'90s to finish in the top 10 in wins (No.5 with 720, tied with
Boston) but have no postseason victories in the decade.
</P>
<P>
   __Of the top-grossing contemporary sports movies, Adam Sandler's
``The Waterboy'' ranks second (behind ``Jerry Maguire'') and ahead
of all four ``Rocky'' movies.
</P>
<P>
   __After Michael Jordan (46) and Muhammad Ali (35), the next two
athletes most frequently seen on the cover of Sports Illustrated
are Kareem Abdul-Jabbar (28) and Magic Johnson (24).
</P>
<P>
   __The NHL single-game record for most penalty minutes assessed
to one player is 67 by the Kings' Randy Holt against the
Philadelphia Flyers in 1979. No.2 on the list with 55 is the
Flyers' Frank Bathe. In the same game, of course.
</P>
<P>
   Both were given three majors and two 10-minute misconducts, but
Holt received one more game misconduct (three, to Bathe's two),
plus one minor penalty to beat him to the punch. And to the top of
the list.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
