another company that then used the information to sell the
customers insurance. The company, Benefit Consultants Inc.,
encrypted each bank account number in a way it thought would not be
identifiable without a special code. But one of Heritage's
customers, Albert Newman, was able to deciper the code. He was
outraged and ordered his bank not to give out the numbers. He
finally ended up suing his bank.
